Done. Here's a summary of the change:

**What changed**: `src/commands_state.rs` — replaced the unbounded `read_events(&path)` call in `handle_state_summary` (line 1307) with a cheap streaming line count via `BufRead::lines()`. Also added `use std::io::BufRead;` import.

**Why**: The old code loaded all ~158K JSON events into memory just to display the total count in a progress note. This caused the command to time out at 10s, blocking diagnostic commands during sessions.

**Verification**:
• `cargo fmt -- --check` ✓
• `cargo build` ✓
• `timeout 10 ./target/debug/yyds state summary` — completes instantly, shows `88544 total` ✓
• `cargo test commands_state -- --test-threads=1` — 176 passed, 0 failed ✓
• `git diff --name-only` — only `src/commands_state.rs` ✓

**How it works**: Instead of parsing all JSON events to count them, the fix counts lines in the events file directly. Since yyds state events are always single-line JSON, line count == event count. `BufRead::lines()` streams through the file without loading it all into memory.

